WEBVTT

01:40.938 --> 01:42.356
All right, mama.

01:43.148 --> 01:44.400
You look well.

01:44.400 --> 01:45.526
- Okay.
I do?

01:45.526 --> 01:47.278
Yes, you do. You look nice.

01:47.278 --> 01:49.446
It's a lot.
It is a lot.

02:00.040 --> 02:01.250
Okay.

02:01.250 --> 02:02.584
You like isolation, huh?

02:06.213 --> 02:09.049
You want a special invitation?
Get your ass in the line. Let's go!

02:09.049 --> 02:10.801
Fuck off! Don't come over here.

02:34.783 --> 02:36.535
Ain't no damn way
you coming back up in here.

02:36.535 --> 02:37.911
- Why not?
- Back up.

02:40.748 --> 02:43.083
I was wondering
why the hell you disappeared.

02:43.751 --> 02:46.754
RAP sheet as long
as a goddamned sidewalk.

02:46.754 --> 02:48.756
I'ma call the cops,
you keep standing there.

02:48.756 --> 02:50.883
All right, well,
then give me my two weeks back.

02:50.883 --> 02:53.802
- From a year and a half ago?
- Then give me my job back.

02:54.428 --> 02:55.930
You know what?

02:57.431 --> 02:58.766
Here. Here-- Here you go.

02:59.767 --> 03:01.018
That good enough for you?

03:05.439 --> 03:07.900
Is that Inez?

03:08.525 --> 03:11.946
- Oh, my God!
- How you doing, mama?

03:13.072 --> 03:14.531
I thought you moved
to another shelter.

03:14.531 --> 03:16.033
No, you know I was in Rikers.

03:16.033 --> 03:18.160
They had me in there
for boosting and shit.

03:18.160 --> 03:19.912
Can't wait for you
to get at this hair, though.

03:19.912 --> 03:22.331
If I go get the dye,
will you please do it for me next week?

03:22.331 --> 03:23.999
I really missed you, girl.

03:23.999 --> 03:25.376
Yeah, and apparently these roots too.

03:25.376 --> 03:26.585
- What you been doing?

03:26.585 --> 03:28.045
- What she been doing?
Nothing.

03:28.045 --> 03:29.338
Yes, the roots missed you too.

03:29.338 --> 03:30.422
Terry, hurry up!

03:30.422 --> 03:31.507
Hey-hey-hey-hey...

03:31.507 --> 03:34.051
You ain't getting nothing from
the store if you keep acting like that!

03:34.051 --> 03:36.428
Inez, whatever happened
to that scammer you was fucking with?

03:36.428 --> 03:38.013
You ever hear from him?

03:38.013 --> 03:39.348
We missed you, yo.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.477
Terry.

03:46.146 --> 03:47.648
You don't hear me calling you?

03:49.984 --> 03:51.777
You don't remember me now?

03:53.237 --> 03:56.240
Just let me see your eyes, T,
so I know you're not mad at me.

03:57.199 --> 03:58.742
He not gonna answer.

03:58.742 --> 04:00.828
I'm back across the street
at the shelter.

04:00.828 --> 04:03.163
And, look,
I'm staying out of trouble this time.

04:03.163 --> 04:06.041
I'ma be around here for good now.
You hear that, T?

04:07.835 --> 04:09.837
Just want to make sure you're doing okay.

04:12.256 --> 04:15.175
Here. Get you another Icee.

04:15.175 --> 04:17.302
Look, y'all keep this between us, aight?

04:17.970 --> 04:19.804
Don't let nobody know I came by here.

04:19.804 --> 04:20.931
Okay.

04:22.308 --> 04:24.560
You're pretty.
See y'all around.

04:25.519 --> 04:27.479
Man, stop flirting with people.

04:42.119 --> 04:44.580
Hey! Hey-hey-hey! None of that!

04:44.580 --> 04:47.249
Get up. Get up. Okay, let's go!

04:47.249 --> 04:51.211
Everybody, if you don't know how to act,
then we not coming to the park!

04:51.837 --> 04:53.464
Turn around. Let's go!

05:02.890 --> 05:05.809
I got the perms, the hairs, the weaves!

05:05.809 --> 05:08.312
Fuck off the street!
- Wash and dry.

05:08.312 --> 05:11.482
- I know you want that hair done.
Next time, I'ma hit you!

05:11.482 --> 05:12.650
Hey-hey-hey, ma-ma-ma-ma!

05:12.650 --> 05:13.984
- Excuse me, excuse me.

05:13.984 --> 05:15.361
Hold on. Slow down.

05:15.361 --> 05:17.196
Hey, you know you want me
to do your hair.

05:17.196 --> 05:19.990
Bitch, move!
What the fuck is wrong with you?

05:21.450 --> 05:22.701
Thank you, baby.

05:23.744 --> 05:24.954
Hey, come here.

05:25.579 --> 05:26.580
How are you?

05:26.580 --> 05:29.458
I want to take this French roll out
and put me some length in.

05:29.458 --> 05:31.543
Yeah, you know, I do braids for 75.

05:31.543 --> 05:32.670
- Call me.
- All right.

05:32.670 --> 05:34.296
My number's right there, right there.

05:35.130 --> 05:36.173
Aight.

05:36.173 --> 05:38.259
I'm about to ask y'all
a serious question.

05:38.259 --> 05:40.511
Who is y'all best player of all time?

05:40.511 --> 05:42.513
Bro, what?

05:43.555 --> 05:45.683
- Michael Jordan!

05:46.725 --> 05:47.935
Shawn.
- Huh? Oh. Oh, hi.

05:47.935 --> 05:49.687
How's your friend doing?
I need to know he's okay.

05:49.687 --> 05:51.480
Terry not here no more.
Stop asking!

05:51.480 --> 05:52.940
Well, figure out a better answer.

05:53.816 --> 05:56.568
Now, if I tell you, what you gonna gimme?

05:59.029 --> 06:00.698
- Here.
- Thank you.

06:00.698 --> 06:01.782
Now what's up?

06:02.408 --> 06:03.450
He at the hospital.

06:03.951 --> 06:06.078
The hospital? Why?
What happened?

06:06.078 --> 06:07.663
Running from our foster mother.

06:07.663 --> 06:10.416
Fell out the window, hit his head.

06:19.174 --> 06:20.175
Let me see.

06:24.430 --> 06:25.472
It hurt?

06:27.391 --> 06:29.810
You know, you could've died
doing something like that?

06:37.818 --> 06:39.653
What's wrong with the one I gave you?

06:39.653 --> 06:40.946
It's corny.

06:41.780 --> 06:44.199
All right, well,
then buy your own fucking toy, then.

06:51.790 --> 06:52.875
What you like?

06:54.793 --> 06:56.503
Power Rangers.

07:01.300 --> 07:03.010
Tell me more
about your foster mother.

07:03.010 --> 07:04.136
You like her?

07:09.642 --> 07:11.644
She probably gone anyway.

07:12.478 --> 07:15.689
When I was in foster care,
stuff like this happened all the time.

07:17.942 --> 07:19.860
My sister used to look out for me.

07:20.653 --> 07:22.279
But she ran away.

07:22.279 --> 07:23.864
Where's she at now?

07:25.115 --> 07:26.200
I don't know.

07:28.118 --> 07:29.495
I can't find her.

07:31.121 --> 07:33.040
My family's gone, boo.

07:43.384 --> 07:46.178
You left me on the street corner?

07:51.684 --> 07:53.560
Who would tell you something like that?

07:55.020 --> 07:57.231
Why the fuck would they tell you
some shit like that?

08:02.736 --> 08:04.071
Get that out your head.

08:16.959 --> 08:18.836
Hey, yo, what's up, ma?
What you doing?

08:18.836 --> 08:21.422
Pushing my way. Where you going?
What's happenin'?

08:21.422 --> 08:25.301
Yo, he got his feelings hurt.
He got his feelings hurt.

09:05.132 --> 09:06.300
Wow, really?

09:07.635 --> 09:09.345
Hold up. Hold up, hold up, hold up.

09:10.679 --> 09:11.722
Want to split this?

09:11.722 --> 09:12.806
Yeah.

09:14.350 --> 09:15.559
Okay.

09:28.989 --> 09:30.407
Um,

09:30.407 --> 09:31.492
T...

09:33.369 --> 09:36.413
I just wanted to come say bye.

09:36.413 --> 09:38.040
Just for a little while.

09:38.040 --> 09:39.583
Um...

09:39.583 --> 09:41.043
I think they gonna move you.

09:42.836 --> 09:46.173
I don't know where yet,

09:46.840 --> 09:48.175
but I'll see you soon.

09:58.352 --> 10:00.187
Save my beeper number,

10:01.605 --> 10:03.065
just in case,

10:04.692 --> 10:06.318
till I find you, okay?

10:10.406 --> 10:11.490
When?

10:15.035 --> 10:16.203
I don't know yet.

10:21.417 --> 10:23.627
Why you keep leaving me?

10:38.851 --> 10:42.563
Well, that means you have bad luck,

10:42.563 --> 10:47.651
because I'm about to do a karate kick!

10:48.652 --> 10:50.404
Pow! Pow!

11:25.022 --> 11:27.733
Would it make you feel better
if you came to stay with me?

11:29.401 --> 11:31.278
Just for a couple days?

11:31.904 --> 11:33.364
Yeah.

11:33.364 --> 11:35.616
<i>♪ Oh, yeah, coming through
With my Shaolin crew... ♪</i>

11:35.616 --> 11:38.452
All right, we gonna go to Harlem
where I grew up at.

11:38.452 --> 11:41.163
<i>♪ In the midst of broken bottles
And crushed-up cans ♪</i>

11:41.163 --> 11:44.917
<i>♪ Meth Tical's in the jam
Oh, how dry I am ♪</i>

11:44.917 --> 11:47.127
<i>♪ With St. Ides in my system ♪</i>

11:47.127 --> 11:49.380
<i>♪ Crack another, I'm blessed
Let's go get the next one ♪</i>

11:49.380 --> 11:52.174
<i>♪ And get over
The object is to stay sober... ♪</i>

11:54.051 --> 11:57.471
<i>♪ Call me the Wallabee Champ
Stressed out, could never be, son ♪</i>

11:57.471 --> 11:59.848
<i>♪ Ricochet daily
Hit the deli for a cold one ♪</i>

11:59.848 --> 12:02.559
<i>♪ Naturally blessed, yes
My rap is like a laser beam... ♪</i>

12:02.559 --> 12:04.687
Yo, look how big
this man's head is.

12:09.191 --> 12:11.485
You want to see New York
turn into the suburbs?

12:19.451 --> 12:21.328
- How's the pizza?
- Good.

12:29.336 --> 12:30.671
Where's my dad at?

12:34.633 --> 12:36.051
He's gone.

12:38.178 --> 12:41.181
You wouldn't have liked him anyway.
I got somebody else in mind.

12:47.438 --> 12:48.689
You miss your old friends?

12:48.689 --> 12:50.441
They're not my friends.

12:51.275 --> 12:54.570
Yeah. Sometimes
I feel like I ain't got no friends either.

12:57.865 --> 12:58.866
Except you.

13:04.204 --> 13:05.205
Ugh.

13:27.937 --> 13:29.563
How much longer?

13:32.149 --> 13:35.194
- How much longer?

13:35.194 --> 13:36.946
<i>We're sorry.</i>

13:36.946 --> 13:39.490
- How much--
- Terry, just gimme a minute, please.

13:39.490 --> 13:40.866
We gonna sleep out here?

13:40.866 --> 13:42.159
- You want to?
- No.

13:42.159 --> 13:44.620
All right, then shut the fuck up
and let me finish!

13:44.620 --> 13:46.038
<i>...and try your call again.</i>

13:47.706 --> 13:50.084
- Sorry for cursing.

13:50.084 --> 13:52.670
Damn, Terry! Just go, go.
Go back to Brooklyn.

13:52.670 --> 13:54.838
- Go back to Brooklyn!
- I don't want to go back!

13:54.838 --> 13:58.008
- I'll call your social workers right now!
- I want to stay with you!

13:58.008 --> 13:59.635
Well, then stop crying
and look at me.

13:59.635 --> 14:02.429
All you got is me. Okay?

14:03.931 --> 14:05.891
I'll go to war for you, you know that?

14:05.891 --> 14:08.560
Do you understand that?
Against anybody.

14:08.560 --> 14:11.188
Against this whole fucked-up city.

14:11.188 --> 14:12.564
They can try all they want.

14:12.564 --> 14:15.985
They can try all they want,
but they not breaking us up this time.

14:17.069 --> 14:18.612
You want to find a new home?

14:19.363 --> 14:20.364
Hmm?

14:20.364 --> 14:22.157
Yes.

14:22.157 --> 14:24.451
But I need to know
we in this thing together.

14:25.286 --> 14:26.495
Tell me.

14:26.495 --> 14:29.540
- We're in this together.
- Tell me!

14:29.540 --> 14:31.333
We're in this together!

14:55.232 --> 14:56.275
<i>Hello?</i>

14:56.275 --> 14:58.277
Kim? Boo, it's Inez.

14:58.277 --> 15:00.529
Oh, my God,
thank God you got the same number.

15:00.529 --> 15:01.989
Listen, I'm uptown.

15:10.623 --> 15:13.584
Y'all go sit in the living room
while I talk to her real quick.

15:13.584 --> 15:15.502
- Is that Ghetto Inez in my living room?
- Shh!

15:15.502 --> 15:17.004
When did you start hanging
with her again?

15:17.004 --> 15:19.465
She's with her son.
Please don't say anything.

15:20.841 --> 15:22.885
She needs a place to stay.

15:24.511 --> 15:26.263
Want to come say hi?

15:26.263 --> 15:28.849
Girl, I'm tired.

15:31.268 --> 15:32.478
For how long?

15:33.354 --> 15:34.813
I don't know.

15:34.813 --> 15:36.857
We'll deal with this tomorrow.

15:39.443 --> 15:41.362
Good morning, sunshine.

15:43.155 --> 15:45.616
If y'all are hungry,
I'ma make breakfast downstairs.

15:45.616 --> 15:47.201
Come on, dance with me.

15:49.870 --> 15:51.956
Oh.

15:51.956 --> 15:54.875
Look at you. Look at you.

15:57.795 --> 15:59.672
You get your GED?

15:59.672 --> 16:02.424
- Inside.
- Really?

16:02.424 --> 16:04.760
Yo, that's fly.

16:04.760 --> 16:07.888
Bruh, you get, like, excited
about the weirdest things.

16:07.888 --> 16:10.099
- I'm proud of you!

16:10.808 --> 16:11.809
So what's your plan?

16:12.393 --> 16:14.853
You up here for good or...

16:15.396 --> 16:18.565
I don't know.
I'm tired of these catty-ass shops.

16:19.858 --> 16:22.486
- Start your own.
- With what money?

16:22.486 --> 16:24.822
What am I supposed to do right now?

16:24.822 --> 16:27.241
Me and my son
need something to eat right now.

16:28.951 --> 16:30.369
Yeah.

16:30.369 --> 16:34.331
You know, I've been meaning
to ask you about Terry.

16:36.083 --> 16:40.004
So, you have him with, uh, Lucky?

16:43.632 --> 16:46.010
Me and Lucky were broken up
when I had T.

16:46.010 --> 16:47.428
He still locked up?

16:48.262 --> 16:49.471
Yeah.

16:49.471 --> 16:51.098
I'll introduce them when he gets out.

17:00.441 --> 17:01.609
The city had him.

17:01.609 --> 17:03.777
He's not supposed
to be with me.

17:05.029 --> 17:07.239
Yo, can't you get locked up
for some shit like that?

17:07.239 --> 17:09.157
Not if you keep it to yourself.

17:15.455 --> 17:16.749
Um...

17:20.961 --> 17:22.253
It's safe with me.

17:31.931 --> 17:33.515
Nez, we good.

17:35.309 --> 17:38.354
Look at the cute little dinosaurs.

17:39.772 --> 17:41.732
- They look dumb.
- Okay, no, they don't.

17:41.732 --> 17:43.484
Stop being mean.

17:45.235 --> 17:46.695
She working?

17:46.695 --> 17:48.989
I think she went job hunting today.

17:49.865 --> 17:52.618
You can't go to anybody's place
looking and talking like that.

17:52.618 --> 17:54.078
And all that yakking.

17:54.078 --> 17:55.996
Ma, she can borrow my stuff.

17:57.456 --> 17:59.625
Terry, you like the coloring books, baby?

18:00.834 --> 18:04.380
Good. You know, when I was your age,
my mother taught me how to read.

18:04.380 --> 18:06.006
She spent a lot of time with me.

18:06.006 --> 18:08.592
Well, let me get a loosie, a Big Burst

18:08.592 --> 18:11.011
and some sunflower seeds,
the nacho cheese ones.

18:12.179 --> 18:14.390
<i>...a six-year-old boy snatched.</i>

18:14.390 --> 18:16.392
<i>Brookdale, one of the city's most troubled</i>

18:16.392 --> 18:19.603
<i>and underfunded hospitals,
reports the child was spending</i>

18:19.603 --> 18:21.647
<i>one of his last mornings in patient care.</i>

18:21.647 --> 18:24.483
Um, they talking about that kid
that got snatched in Brooklyn?

18:25.484 --> 18:27.278
I don't know that story.

18:27.278 --> 18:29.488
All right, matter of fact,
let me get a newspaper too.

18:29.488 --> 18:32.283
<i>...information
to please call Crime Stoppers</i>

18:32.283 --> 18:35.995
<i>at 800-577-1212.</i>

18:49.592 --> 18:50.926
<i>Jones residence.</i>
- Yeah, Kim.

18:50.926 --> 18:53.053
I need you to make sure
you keep Terry in your sight.

18:53.053 --> 18:55.097
-<i>Don't let him out of your sight.</i>
- What?

18:55.889 --> 18:57.766
Just keep him in the house.

18:57.766 --> 19:01.145
- Inez, where are you?
-<i>Just do it! Please, Kim!</i>

19:01.145 --> 19:02.980
<i>I don't want nobody asking questions.</i>

19:02.980 --> 19:05.691
-<i>I got to handle some things.</i>
- Of course.

19:10.404 --> 19:12.072
- She say where she was at?
- Uh-uh.

19:12.072 --> 19:14.950
Doesn't make sense. It doesn't
take this long to look for work.

19:14.950 --> 19:17.411
You like to play games, Terry?
- This is ridiculous.

19:19.580 --> 19:21.248
So quiet.

19:24.293 --> 19:25.836
Who's hiding in there?

19:29.423 --> 19:30.591
Mmm?

19:35.262 --> 19:36.764
I found work.

19:43.729 --> 19:45.856
Come on, boo,
so you can try these on.

19:48.859 --> 19:49.944
You like 'em?

19:51.654 --> 19:53.238
They're too big.

19:53.989 --> 19:55.282
You'll grow into them.

19:57.201 --> 19:58.786
Why don't you take 'em upstairs?

20:04.166 --> 20:06.752
Kim, check the stove for me, please.

20:07.294 --> 20:08.629
Okay.

20:09.296 --> 20:11.215
<i>♪ Pray for you, darlin' ♪</i>

20:11.215 --> 20:15.511
<i>♪ Till you decide to come home... ♪</i>

20:15.511 --> 20:17.930
Can you just at least
act like you see me here?

20:19.014 --> 20:22.268
Exactly what do you expect
and want from me?

20:23.018 --> 20:24.937
Strolling in here
after being God-knows-where...

20:24.937 --> 20:26.146
Doing what I had to.

20:26.146 --> 20:28.148
Like some kind of streetwalker.

20:28.941 --> 20:30.609
What the fuck did you just call me?

20:30.609 --> 20:32.278
Shit.

20:32.278 --> 20:33.696
Run that back again.

20:33.696 --> 20:35.114
Ma, Inez...

20:35.114 --> 20:38.325
You always treated me like I'm not
good enough to be around your daughter.

20:39.451 --> 20:41.870
Whatever you think of me,
just spit it out!

20:41.870 --> 20:43.956
I don't think anything of you.

20:46.500 --> 20:48.085
- Inez, what's up with you?
- What!

20:48.085 --> 20:50.337
- What!
- No! I'm fine.

20:50.879 --> 20:52.840
- Glass almost cut my foot.

20:52.840 --> 20:55.676
Turning my house
into damn 125th Street.

20:56.635 --> 20:58.512
- Ma!
- No, no.

21:02.016 --> 21:04.476
The hell are you teaching
that little boy up there?

21:06.687 --> 21:09.773
Twenty-two years old,
acting like a child.

21:09.773 --> 21:13.027
You want them to take you serious,
be from Harlem, not of Harlem.

21:16.196 --> 21:17.531
So that's it?

21:18.198 --> 21:20.284
You don't have nothing else to say?

21:23.704 --> 21:25.205
- I said I was...
- To me!

21:28.709 --> 21:30.753
Was I wrong? Yes.

21:30.753 --> 21:34.465
But what else do you want me to say?
That I'm nothing? A streetwalker?

21:34.465 --> 21:37.676
You can't keep fighting
everyone you disagree with.

21:38.177 --> 21:40.304
We got to grow up.

21:40.304 --> 21:42.973
Okay, look, my mom's gonna be
who she's gonna be, but, like...

21:42.973 --> 21:44.516
But, like, what?

21:46.060 --> 21:49.563
When are you going to realize
that you are enough?

21:49.563 --> 21:51.357
Who cares what she says?

21:51.357 --> 21:54.818
Why even let any of that shit get to you?

22:00.407 --> 22:01.408
She...

22:03.452 --> 22:05.287
She said I was a bad mother.

22:10.125 --> 22:12.586
Come here. Come here.

22:20.427 --> 22:23.013
She forgets you don't have one.

22:30.562 --> 22:31.563
Hey, you.

22:32.356 --> 22:34.900
You better get that chip
off your shoulder.

22:36.277 --> 22:37.611
I know you hear me.

22:40.155 --> 22:41.156
Come on.

22:46.078 --> 22:48.455
All right, promise me
you're gonna be good for Mommy?

23:17.484 --> 23:18.652
T, don't go up.

23:20.487 --> 23:22.573
We don't really know anybody here.

23:25.326 --> 23:26.327
I lied.

23:33.334 --> 23:35.002
Don't look at me like that.

23:35.002 --> 23:36.170
Get off me.

23:37.504 --> 23:40.299
- Why you being mean to me?
- 'Cause you keep fucking up!

23:40.299 --> 23:41.926
Ow!

23:41.926 --> 23:43.844
Who said you could talk to me like that?

23:43.844 --> 23:46.597
- I liked them!
- Okay, well, yeah. What about me?

23:46.597 --> 23:48.140
What about me, Terry?

23:48.140 --> 23:50.851
Some shit is more important
than some coloring books.

23:59.652 --> 24:01.070
I didn't mean to hurt you.

24:09.787 --> 24:11.538
- Wait right here.

24:22.549 --> 24:24.301
<i>Hey, this is Wanda.</i>

24:24.301 --> 24:26.720
<i>Leave a message after the beep,
and I'll call you back.</i>

24:50.327 --> 24:51.662
<i>Hello?</i>
- Hi. This Cynthia?

24:51.662 --> 24:53.247
-<i>Who this</i>?
- Listen, I need a favor.

24:53.247 --> 24:54.748
-<i>What?</i>
- The building that I'm living in,

24:54.748 --> 24:56.667
it got asbestos,
and they cleared everybody out.

24:56.667 --> 24:58.419
<i>Inez, I'm sorry. You can't stay here.</i>

24:59.753 --> 25:02.381
<i>The number you are calling
is no longer in service.</i>

25:03.299 --> 25:05.134
<i>Hello.</i>
- It's your old hairdresser, Inez.

25:05.134 --> 25:06.552
-<i>You said who?</i>
- Just give me the address,

25:06.552 --> 25:08.554
- and we'll come by later. Terry!
-<i>I did not say...</i>

25:13.392 --> 25:15.227
Terry, are you crazy?
Where were you going!

25:15.227 --> 25:17.396
- Get off me! Get off me!
- Are you crazy?

25:17.396 --> 25:18.939
- Our stuff was in there!

25:56.602 --> 25:58.395
I can't go back to that shelter.

25:59.480 --> 26:00.981
How long you been
on the street?

26:02.107 --> 26:03.108
Long enough.

26:05.986 --> 26:07.112
Where are your people?

26:12.284 --> 26:13.285
Gone.

26:13.911 --> 26:14.912
Gone where?

26:15.704 --> 26:17.206
You from up here?

26:19.792 --> 26:20.918
I lost 'em.

26:21.835 --> 26:23.045
Lost them how?

26:33.681 --> 26:34.682
Yeah.

26:35.683 --> 26:37.059
You and the rest of us.

26:40.521 --> 26:42.648
My baby girl's still struggling.

26:42.648 --> 26:45.192
Her son's about the same age
as your little boy.

26:48.529 --> 26:49.530
Pea?

26:51.073 --> 26:52.283
Pea?

26:52.283 --> 26:54.660
You can take the little room
on the second floor.

26:54.660 --> 26:55.786
Yes?

26:55.786 --> 26:58.622
Clear your things
from Sadie's old room. Mmm?

26:58.622 --> 27:00.040
- Okay?
- Okay.

27:01.083 --> 27:02.835
And like I tell all my tenants,

27:03.544 --> 27:05.713
try anything, I keep a .44 ready.

27:07.631 --> 27:09.425
Go show him where to go, baby.

27:09.425 --> 27:10.551
Is this your house?

27:13.178 --> 27:15.889
Ooh!

27:16.557 --> 27:17.933
Mmm!

27:17.933 --> 27:19.184
Mmm-mmm-mmm-mmm.

27:19.184 --> 27:21.520
Mmm. Girl.

27:22.062 --> 27:23.564
It's nothing.

27:23.564 --> 27:25.399
Does that mean
I don't have to pay you?

27:27.568 --> 27:28.569
Well...

27:29.695 --> 27:31.530
Girl, I feel like something.

27:40.873 --> 27:42.791
- Thank you, sweetie.
- Mm-hmm.

27:47.004 --> 27:48.756
I can't even get it this time.

27:48.756 --> 27:50.466
Where does the rent go?

27:50.466 --> 27:51.800
That-- No.

27:52.635 --> 27:54.762
Just leave it right there.

27:55.429 --> 27:57.014
Got him.

27:57.014 --> 27:58.390
Yeah.

27:59.433 --> 28:00.434
Oh, no, wait.

28:01.560 --> 28:04.104
- You ever see her?
Who? Oh, Crystal?

28:04.104 --> 28:05.439
Yeah, your daughter.

28:06.065 --> 28:07.066
She, um...

28:09.109 --> 28:11.445
She's cleaned up a few times.

28:12.071 --> 28:13.739
That's a battle I can't fight.

28:15.282 --> 28:17.576
She'll come home for good
when she's ready.

28:21.664 --> 28:23.958
By the way,
if you're still looking for better money,

28:23.958 --> 28:28.712
uh, a friend of mine
might have a job for you.

28:28.712 --> 28:30.631
Really? Where at?

28:30.631 --> 28:33.217
Cleaning staff for a nursing home
on Jamaica Avenue.

28:33.217 --> 28:34.969
- In Queens?
- Yes, Queens.

28:34.969 --> 28:36.428
That's, like, a two-hour train ride.

28:36.428 --> 28:39.515
Well...
...do what you want.

28:39.515 --> 28:42.184
Just don't waste anymore time
feeling sorry for yourself.

28:47.481 --> 28:50.567
Your generation don't know
just how good you have it.

28:58.951 --> 29:01.870
<i>Jaywalking is a fact of life here.</i>

29:01.870 --> 29:03.872
<i>"No more," says Mayor Giuliani.</i>

29:03.872 --> 29:05.916
<i>He plans to crack down on pedestrians</i>

29:05.916 --> 29:08.127
<i>who cross where and when
they're not supposed to.</i>

29:08.127 --> 29:10.004
I'll walk where I want to walk!
Motherfucker...

29:10.004 --> 29:11.547
<i>Plan with me</i>

29:11.547 --> 29:13.799
<i>to make the realistic changes</i>

29:13.799 --> 29:16.927
<i>that will actually make people's lives</i>

29:16.927 --> 29:18.887
<i>better than they are right now,</i>

29:18.887 --> 29:21.348
<i>and work hard with me</i>

29:21.348 --> 29:25.185
<i>to apply these plans to improve our city.</i>

29:26.520 --> 29:28.939
<i>Dream, believe,</i>

29:28.939 --> 29:31.275
<i>plan and work.</i>

29:31.275 --> 29:35.154
<i>This is the foundation
for the process of change.</i>

29:49.251 --> 29:50.669
Say, "Hi, Mommy."

29:51.378 --> 29:53.047
- Hey.
- Hi.

29:54.131 --> 29:56.175
Tell Mommy what books we read today.

29:57.509 --> 29:58.594
Hey, girl.

30:12.191 --> 30:13.317
The dash is missing.

30:13.984 --> 30:14.985
Huh?

30:17.404 --> 30:18.822
Never mind.

30:25.955 --> 30:27.498
Yo, how much they charge you?

30:28.248 --> 30:30.668
- 350.
- Okay.

30:30.668 --> 30:32.211
You did good, babe.

30:34.588 --> 30:36.257
How you like the job?

30:39.802 --> 30:41.262
I miss doing hair.

30:45.391 --> 30:47.059
He back in school yet?

30:47.810 --> 30:49.311
Hand me a screw.

30:56.568 --> 30:59.405
Got to get a copy
of his birth certificate and all that.

31:02.116 --> 31:04.285
I, um, started applying too.

31:05.953 --> 31:07.997
I'm going to Clark Atlanta in the fall.

31:09.290 --> 31:11.875
- You leaving us?
- I wouldn't say it like that.

31:18.966 --> 31:21.010
I'm happy for you.

31:21.010 --> 31:22.428
You could go back too.

31:23.762 --> 31:26.223
Even if it's part-time
or something like that.

31:28.142 --> 31:29.768
Yeah, someday.

31:35.024 --> 31:36.066
All right, baby.

31:36.066 --> 31:39.695
You got cereal and milk.
Leftovers is in the fridge.

31:39.695 --> 31:42.197
And don't heat it up
for over 60 seconds,

31:42.197 --> 31:44.074
'cause if you do,
your mouth will get burnt.

31:44.074 --> 31:46.994
And do not answer the door for anybody.

31:47.620 --> 31:48.829
If the phone rings,

31:48.829 --> 31:51.332
wait for the answering machine
to come on to see if it's me.

31:53.459 --> 31:54.543
Okay?

31:56.503 --> 31:58.505
I'll be back from work around 6:00.

32:08.057 --> 32:09.058
Okay?

32:09.600 --> 32:10.601
Be good, boo.

32:33.666 --> 32:37.002
<i>Today the streets
are even more dangerous than you think.</i>

32:37.002 --> 32:38.462
<i>You like flying?</i>

32:38.462 --> 32:41.465
<i>I got something
that'll really make you fly.</i>

32:41.465 --> 32:43.467
<i>So talk to your kids
about drugs, or...</i>

33:04.071 --> 33:06.490
<i>Quincy Jones has made his mark in music</i>

33:06.490 --> 33:09.493
<i>as a composer, conductor
and arranger</i>

33:09.493 --> 33:11.787
<i>during a time
when it was almost unheard of</i>

33:11.787 --> 33:14.415
<i>for a Black composer
to do a Hollywood movie.</i>

33:15.249 --> 33:19.128
<i>The imagination's always been
a comfort zone, safety zone, really,</i>

33:19.128 --> 33:22.506
<i>because it's something you can run to</i>

33:22.506 --> 33:25.092
<i>and make it anything you want, really.</i>

33:46.405 --> 33:47.406
This house look--

33:52.369 --> 33:53.412
Everything okay?

33:59.126 --> 34:01.462
Why nobody looking for me?

34:04.798 --> 34:06.884
Because we made it too hard for them.

34:08.969 --> 34:10.804
That was the whole point, remember?

34:16.142 --> 34:17.144
Come here.

34:25.986 --> 34:26.987
Hey.

34:32.618 --> 34:33.619
Look.

34:34.495 --> 34:36.622
I don't know what the fuck to tell you, T.

34:37.665 --> 34:40.209
But there's more to life
than fucked-up beginnings.

34:44.588 --> 34:46.173
You're not holding it right!

34:47.548 --> 34:49.677
Hey, talk to me nice. I got this.

34:51.135 --> 34:52.095
You ready?

34:52.095 --> 34:53.805
You ready-ready?

34:57.517 --> 34:58.936
Yeah!

34:58.936 --> 35:01.105
You did it! You did it! You did it!

35:04.650 --> 35:06.360
You gonna throw it all the way over--

35:10.572 --> 35:12.324
Throw that thing better than that.

35:18.789 --> 35:21.375
Now you just being lazy.

35:23.377 --> 35:24.378
You ready?

35:25.796 --> 35:26.797
Yeah.

35:27.756 --> 35:28.799
Mmm.

35:32.469 --> 35:33.637
Ooh!

35:33.637 --> 35:35.347
Okay, yeah, you did it.

35:37.933 --> 35:40.019
I never had my own room growing up.

35:40.936 --> 35:42.187
You wanna try?

35:43.147 --> 35:44.815
Who lived here before us?

35:45.899 --> 35:47.651
I don't know. A bunch of immigrants.

35:47.651 --> 35:49.987
- And before them?
- I don't know, baby.

35:49.987 --> 35:52.072
We can go to the library
and look it up.

35:53.282 --> 35:56.493
Down and up. Down--

36:06.920 --> 36:07.922
Who's that?

36:12.635 --> 36:13.969
This is me.

36:14.845 --> 36:17.222
When I was first coming out
of the group home.

36:18.057 --> 36:19.183
Cute little thing.

36:23.854 --> 36:26.899
My body was a playground for
a thousand niggas before you came along.

36:26.899 --> 36:28.317
- That's nasty.

36:28.317 --> 36:29.860
Hey, I got more of us,

36:29.860 --> 36:32.321
but things get lost
when we moving around so much.

36:32.321 --> 36:34.281
Yo. Open up.
- Hold on, hold on.

36:35.324 --> 36:36.533
It's Rudy.

36:38.285 --> 36:39.954
- Hello.
- Hey.

36:45.000 --> 36:47.753
My bad I'm late.
Some of the papers took longer to get.

36:47.753 --> 36:49.713
What if he needs to go
to the doctor?

36:49.713 --> 36:52.049
Just show up and say he's sick.

36:52.049 --> 36:54.176
And I got one for the city
so it looks legit.

36:54.176 --> 36:55.261
Okay.

36:56.303 --> 36:58.472
Hotbox, numbers.

36:59.431 --> 37:01.392
- Whatever you need, hit me up.
- Okay.

37:01.392 --> 37:02.768
- Okay?
- Okay.

37:07.898 --> 37:11.944
Okay, I went with Daryl,
last name Raymond.

37:11.944 --> 37:14.321
We just moved in from Jersey.

37:14.321 --> 37:16.615
- Your middle name is Terry.

37:16.615 --> 37:18.117
I don't like it.

37:21.954 --> 37:22.955
Hi, Kim.

37:26.709 --> 37:27.960
Daryl Raymond.

37:27.960 --> 37:31.255
<i>...three, two, one. Now!</i>

37:46.687 --> 37:47.688
That's him?

37:53.277 --> 37:55.321
Why you standing there
looking scared?

37:59.366 --> 38:02.369
Neighbor down the hall
walks him home for me after school.

38:04.496 --> 38:06.749
Terry, I want you to meet Lucky.

38:13.213 --> 38:14.214
Hey, Lucky.

38:15.883 --> 38:17.217
What's up, little man?

38:17.927 --> 38:19.887
Lucky's gonna be moving in with us.

38:21.680 --> 38:22.890
For how long?

38:24.892 --> 38:26.018
Damn.

38:29.229 --> 38:32.149
Little nigga trying
to kick me out already.

38:32.149 --> 38:33.400
Come here.

38:40.074 --> 38:41.575
What's this cut on your face?

38:49.333 --> 38:52.586
Let me get one for good luck, babe.
Let me get one for good luck.

38:52.586 --> 38:53.837
Mmm, mmm-mmm-mmm.

38:53.837 --> 38:56.966
You can get a shot. You want a shot?
You can get a shot. Go ahead. Take a shot.

38:57.675 --> 38:59.927
Terry! Terry!

38:59.927 --> 39:01.095
Yeah, get it, Pea!

39:01.095 --> 39:02.680
- Pea, out! Pea, out!
Out of my kitchen!

39:02.680 --> 39:05.140
- Out of my kitchen!
Look at the D! Look at the D!

39:05.140 --> 39:06.934
Good job, Pea.

39:09.937 --> 39:11.730
Shoot! Pass it. Pass it.

39:11.730 --> 39:13.190
- Let me get another.
- No.

39:13.190 --> 39:14.275
Pass it.

39:16.277 --> 39:17.695
Want to go again?

39:20.239 --> 39:21.615
What's wrong?

39:36.964 --> 39:38.382
Where was he before?

39:40.092 --> 39:41.927
How many times
you gonna ask me that?

39:41.927 --> 39:43.095
Till I get an answer.

39:46.098 --> 39:48.309
He belongs with his mother.

39:49.143 --> 39:50.436
Nobody's even looking for him.

39:51.145 --> 39:53.564
Course they're not looking for him
because they're looking for me.

39:53.564 --> 39:56.317
And every other nigga round here
with a target on they back.

39:56.817 --> 39:59.194
Hey, how many times
I been locked up for you, Lucky?

39:59.194 --> 40:00.821
I just got out, man!

40:01.822 --> 40:04.241
Trying to move on from all that shit.

40:04.241 --> 40:07.328
Do you remember what it felt like
to grow up without a father?

40:10.623 --> 40:13.500
Just want us to be a family. That's all.

40:15.461 --> 40:17.046
That's not my fucking kid.

40:19.798 --> 40:21.175
I just wanted you.

40:26.013 --> 40:27.598
But you fucked up in the head.

40:27.598 --> 40:30.351
Yeah, nuts for thinking
you would fucking understand.

40:30.351 --> 40:32.227
I didn't sign up for this shit.

40:39.860 --> 40:41.820
"You are not a cow."

40:41.820 --> 40:45.950
"You are not a boat
or a plane or a snore."

40:45.950 --> 40:47.618
-"Snort."
-"Snort."

40:48.577 --> 40:51.622
- Stop.
-<i>"You are not a boat."</i>

40:51.622 --> 40:53.791
-"Or..."
-"Or a plane

40:53.791 --> 40:55.626
- or a snort."
-"Snort."

40:57.878 --> 40:59.713
"You are my mother."

40:59.713 --> 41:02.299
"You are a bird,

41:02.299 --> 41:03.968
and you are my mother."

41:03.968 --> 41:05.386
Yeah.

41:06.053 --> 41:09.098
"And you are my mother.

41:09.098 --> 41:11.684
And you are my mother.
And you are..."

41:51.056 --> 41:54.101
I literally saw you look at her
with my own eyes.

41:56.437 --> 41:58.063
Is it 'cause she lighter than me?

41:58.939 --> 42:01.191
- 'Cause her hair's nicer?
- You're too sensitive.

42:01.191 --> 42:03.402
Well, then just be sensitive
to my sensitivity.

42:08.907 --> 42:10.784
Where'd you stay this whole time?

42:12.119 --> 42:14.163
Was posted up with Mike.

42:14.163 --> 42:17.082
- That bike not hot, is it?
- No.

42:20.753 --> 42:21.795
One.

42:25.132 --> 42:26.842
All right,
I need another can of broth.

42:29.011 --> 42:30.721
Come on, let me do that after the game.

42:30.721 --> 42:32.640
No. Can you go now?

42:33.349 --> 42:35.309
And why don't you take Terry with you?

42:59.583 --> 43:01.168
How you doing, Lucky?

43:01.168 --> 43:03.379
I'm good, 'Licia.
How you doing, shorty?

43:03.379 --> 43:04.588
You should call me.

43:10.302 --> 43:11.762
Do me a favor.

43:11.762 --> 43:13.555
Walk on this side of me.

43:14.682 --> 43:16.058
It's for your protection.

43:23.148 --> 43:24.525
You always this quiet?

43:28.404 --> 43:29.822
Sometimes.

43:30.447 --> 43:32.157
And what you thinking about?

43:34.368 --> 43:35.869
Well, it sounds like a lot.

43:38.330 --> 43:40.708
How did you get that name Lucky?

43:42.918 --> 43:44.712
Made a few mistakes, that's all.

43:45.713 --> 43:47.339
That's a story for another time.

43:48.382 --> 43:51.594
- And I'm a mistake too?
- Who told you that?

43:51.594 --> 43:53.637
It's why you don't want me around.

43:53.637 --> 43:54.722
That's not true.

43:57.057 --> 43:58.058
You're a blessing.

43:58.851 --> 44:00.352
For your mom especially.

44:02.062 --> 44:03.105
Everything is just...

44:06.233 --> 44:07.693
just complicated.

44:09.194 --> 44:10.988
Aight? Come on.

44:23.208 --> 44:24.668
How'd you get that one?

44:31.258 --> 44:33.010
Guy cut me with a knife.

44:33.010 --> 44:34.094
Why?

44:42.061 --> 44:43.479
He wanted something I took.

45:00.496 --> 45:01.705
You see this one right here?

45:02.957 --> 45:03.958
See it?

45:06.168 --> 45:07.711
On the East Side,

45:07.711 --> 45:10.297
everybody hide they box cutters
right here.

45:10.839 --> 45:12.216
It hurt?

45:14.802 --> 45:16.178
Yeah, a little bit.

45:22.893 --> 45:25.646
<i>HOT 97.</i>

45:34.613 --> 45:36.407
Everything's changing.

45:37.324 --> 45:38.742
A couple of years from now,

45:38.742 --> 45:41.120
we're not gonna have to worry
about this at all.

45:57.219 --> 46:00.097
What do two crooks know
about raising a family?

46:10.190 --> 46:11.358
<i>Yeah!</i>

46:12.192 --> 46:13.319
<i>Yes!</i>

46:13.319 --> 46:14.862
Let me get a picture.

46:14.862 --> 46:16.905
Girl,
he holding you like he love you, okay?

46:16.905 --> 46:18.198
- Terry, now!

46:18.198 --> 46:21.410
And we on the block
right now celebrating.

46:21.410 --> 46:24.038
Shout-out to the newlyweds,
Lucky and Inez.

46:24.038 --> 46:26.665
Yes, girl, show me the ring!
Okay! All right!

46:29.043 --> 46:30.544
What the ring like?

46:31.086 --> 46:33.130
That's exactly
what we bringing here to the block.

46:33.130 --> 46:34.506
Right here, right now.

46:34.506 --> 46:36.967
Come get a plate. Come get a cup.

46:36.967 --> 46:40.095
Come get whatever you need,
and come rock out with your boy.

46:40.095 --> 46:41.263
Come here.

46:42.056 --> 46:44.558
You look good, ma.
You look good!

46:46.185 --> 46:47.186
T...

46:50.689 --> 46:52.149
your mother's my wife now.

46:53.859 --> 46:56.028
But I want you to know
from the bottom of my heart

46:56.028 --> 46:57.696
that I'm here for the both of you.

47:00.532 --> 47:01.825
We blood now.

47:05.079 --> 47:06.747
You scared
I'ma take her away from you?

47:06.747 --> 47:07.957
No.

47:09.583 --> 47:11.710
Nobody's going anywhere,
from this point on.

47:13.754 --> 47:15.714
I promise
to protect you and your mother.

47:16.882 --> 47:17.925
You understand?

47:18.926 --> 47:19.969
Yes.

47:20.928 --> 47:23.180
We're gonna give you
the life that we never had.

47:24.932 --> 47:27.726
Aight? You hear me?

47:28.269 --> 47:29.395
Mmm?

47:31.772 --> 47:32.856
Come here.

47:37.778 --> 47:40.531
Up-up-up. There we go. There we go.

47:40.531 --> 47:42.783
Girl, you got you a family now.

47:42.783 --> 47:45.327
Whoo!

47:45.327 --> 47:47.621
King of the world!

47:47.621 --> 47:48.664
Aw.

47:48.664 --> 47:50.666
We got to get this.
Hold on, hold on. Here we go.

47:50.666 --> 47:51.959
Wait.
- Look at the camera, T.

47:51.959 --> 47:53.836
- Look at the camera.
- Ready?

47:53.836 --> 47:54.962
Ah!

47:55.671 --> 47:57.047
Say, "Family!"

47:57.047 --> 47:58.257
Family.

48:04.763 --> 48:06.265
I'm so happy for y'all.

48:21.989 --> 48:23.157
Let me see.

48:41.300 --> 48:42.760
What you want to hear?

48:43.802 --> 48:45.846
- That one.

48:46.764 --> 48:49.516
<i>If Federal Court
lets new zoning laws take effect,</i>

48:49.516 --> 48:50.601
