I don't wanna talk to you about Lucky.

1:27:20.911 --> 1:27:22.037
It's not about him.

1:27:22.037 --> 1:27:24.456
Yo, I don't wanna talk to you
about anything!

1:27:25.958 --> 1:27:26.959
Yeah?

1:27:28.085 --> 1:27:31.839
Only thing I ever wanted more
than a mother was a fucking father!

1:27:38.304 --> 1:27:39.388
Maybe...

1:27:41.849 --> 1:27:44.268
Maybe if you--
if you weren't so hard on him,

1:27:44.268 --> 1:27:45.936
walking around here
so miserable all the time,

1:27:45.936 --> 1:27:47.688
he'd still fucking be here!

1:27:50.608 --> 1:27:51.734
Hmm.

1:28:00.367 --> 1:28:01.660
You don't mean that.

1:28:20.220 --> 1:28:23.766
<i>♪ ...every now and then ♪</i>

1:28:23.766 --> 1:28:27.269
<i>♪ I'm so high ♪</i>

1:28:28.812 --> 1:28:32.441
<i>♪ Knowing there's a chance I'll see you ♪</i>

1:28:32.441 --> 1:28:36.612
<i>♪ Feel like I could fly ♪</i>

1:28:37.237 --> 1:28:41.200
<i>♪ 'Cause tonight I will be near you ♪</i>

1:28:41.200 --> 1:28:44.119
<i>♪ We will be one ♪</i>

1:28:44.119 --> 1:28:46.330
<i>♪ We'll be alone... ♪</i>

1:28:48.040 --> 1:28:49.041
Yo, Ma.

1:28:50.334 --> 1:28:52.544
- Ma.
- What?

1:28:53.462 --> 1:28:56.340
This lady over there,
she keep looking over here.

1:28:56.340 --> 1:28:57.508
Who is that?

1:29:00.803 --> 1:29:03.055
That's Lucky's daughter
and her mother.

1:29:05.891 --> 1:29:07.434
Make 'em a plate.

1:29:08.769 --> 1:29:09.770
She's what?

1:29:11.105 --> 1:29:12.439
We'll talk about it later.

1:29:49.184 --> 1:29:50.269
Fuck!

1:29:53.314 --> 1:29:55.524
- Terry!
- Ma, what happened?

1:29:55.524 --> 1:29:56.900
Come move this stuff!

1:29:58.235 --> 1:30:00.112
One of the pipes!

1:30:00.112 --> 1:30:01.196
I-- I got it!

1:30:01.989 --> 1:30:04.033
Ma! Yo.

1:30:04.033 --> 1:30:05.326
Come on, come on.

1:30:21.842 --> 1:30:22.843
Sweetheart.

1:30:25.512 --> 1:30:27.014
You seen Javier?

1:30:27.014 --> 1:30:29.224
- Who?
- The super.

1:30:29.224 --> 1:30:31.435
Oh, um, not since yesterday.

1:30:32.186 --> 1:30:33.187
Sorry.

1:30:44.198 --> 1:30:46.075
Daryl, we need to talk.

1:30:46.075 --> 1:30:47.701
Your paperwork was denied.

1:30:49.119 --> 1:30:50.287
What?

1:30:50.287 --> 1:30:53.290
The Social Security number
you gave me isn't valid.

1:30:53.290 --> 1:30:55.459
I'm glad I caught it
before somebody else did.

1:30:55.459 --> 1:30:58.671
Yeah-- I-- I forgot. It-- It expired.

1:30:59.463 --> 1:31:01.048
That's not how it works.

1:31:01.882 --> 1:31:06.136
So, then wh--
That mean, like, I don't get the job or...

1:31:06.136 --> 1:31:08.305
Well, before I can even look
into any of that,

1:31:08.305 --> 1:31:11.600
we need to sort out
how you ended up with phony papers.

1:31:12.184 --> 1:31:13.811
Did you really ask your mom?

1:31:17.231 --> 1:31:19.316
She don't-- She don't have 'em.

1:31:20.567 --> 1:31:21.860
You're from here, right?

1:31:23.237 --> 1:31:25.739
- What you mean?
- Born in the States.

1:31:26.782 --> 1:31:29.952
Yea-- Yeah. Nah, yeah, yeah.

1:31:30.744 --> 1:31:34.123
Well...
...this could mean a lot of hell for you.

1:31:34.123 --> 1:31:36.292
To get a job, to do anything.

1:31:36.292 --> 1:31:39.461
I mean, it's still probably, you know,
like, with the city.

1:31:40.254 --> 1:31:42.590
From when I was in foster care.

1:31:45.009 --> 1:31:46.093
Huh.

1:31:50.139 --> 1:31:52.975
Oh, I have a friend
down in Social Services who can help.

1:31:52.975 --> 1:31:55.019
No, no, it's cool, it's cool, it's cool.

1:31:55.019 --> 1:31:57.021
It's all good. It's all good.
We just-- It's all good.

1:31:57.021 --> 1:31:58.856
Hey, Janice.

1:31:59.773 --> 1:32:02.318
Listen, I need a favor.
I have a student here whose paperwork is...

1:32:02.318 --> 1:32:04.945
Hey, no, no.
Hey, yo, yo, Ms. Tucker, come on!

1:32:07.781 --> 1:32:09.408
It's all-- It's all good.

1:32:12.286 --> 1:32:13.454
Um...

1:32:15.414 --> 1:32:18.208
They-- They don't--
They don't know I'm with my mother.

1:32:18.208 --> 1:32:19.501
- You know?
- And why is that?

1:32:19.501 --> 1:32:21.170
Who are you supposed to be with?

1:32:22.671 --> 1:32:25.049
- Um...
- Have you told anyone else about this?

1:32:27.134 --> 1:32:29.803
- Nah.
- Is Daryl your real name?

1:32:31.972 --> 1:32:34.642
If you lied on your college applications,
it's a felony.

1:32:34.642 --> 1:32:35.893
It's Terry!

1:32:43.484 --> 1:32:45.778
It's-- It's Terry Wallace.

1:32:50.824 --> 1:32:52.534
How long ago did this happen?

1:32:56.455 --> 1:32:58.123
When-- When I was little.

1:33:00.000 --> 1:33:01.961
I was a social worker for years.

1:33:02.670 --> 1:33:06.382
If the city didn't want to give you back,
it's likely because something happened.

1:33:06.382 --> 1:33:09.551
Regardless of what,
you are still a ward of the state.

1:33:09.551 --> 1:33:11.428
By law, I have to report this.

1:33:11.428 --> 1:33:14.265
No. Do any of that even matter, though?

1:33:14.265 --> 1:33:16.892
You know, I'm finna be 18
in a few weeks, you know, so...

1:33:16.892 --> 1:33:18.143
I can't keep this to myself.

1:33:19.144 --> 1:33:20.729
I have to speak with your mother.

1:33:33.409 --> 1:33:36.370
- Can I talk to you?
- It'd be nicer if you could help.

1:33:37.663 --> 1:33:39.873
- What happened?
- What does it look like, Terry?

1:33:40.833 --> 1:33:43.002
Called the super ten times
since yesterday.

1:33:44.378 --> 1:33:45.921
It's about the job with Ms. Tucker.

1:33:45.921 --> 1:33:49.758
She, um-- She want
my birth certificate and my Social.

1:33:49.758 --> 1:33:51.594
The real ones.

1:33:51.594 --> 1:33:53.053
What do you mean, the real one?

1:33:53.053 --> 1:33:55.264
The papers I found in your room,
they didn't work--

1:33:55.264 --> 1:33:57.558
What do you mean, the papers you found
in my room? You went through my stuff?

1:33:57.558 --> 1:33:59.893
- Why wouldn't you ask me?
- I didn't know I had to!

1:34:01.687 --> 1:34:05.024
She want to come by tomorrow evening
and talk to you.

1:34:05.024 --> 1:34:06.108
For what?

1:34:06.108 --> 1:34:08.944
Well, I mean, I don't know.
What was I supposed to say?

1:34:16.035 --> 1:34:18.412
I don't know how the hell
we gonna get ahold of those.

1:34:24.460 --> 1:34:25.878
Come with me outside. I...

1:34:27.379 --> 1:34:28.505
I need to smoke.

1:34:29.590 --> 1:34:31.508
Starting to smell in here.

1:34:44.772 --> 1:34:46.148
You wanted to leave me.

1:34:49.068 --> 1:34:50.069
No.

1:34:51.695 --> 1:34:52.780
No, Ma.

1:34:53.697 --> 1:34:55.449
Why would you say something like that?

1:34:57.910 --> 1:34:58.911
Forget it.

1:35:03.832 --> 1:35:05.960
What time
your teacher coming tomorrow?

1:35:05.960 --> 1:35:08.963
- Around 6:00 or something. I think.

1:35:17.137 --> 1:35:18.180
T, you should probably see

1:35:18.180 --> 1:35:21.767
if you can stay with Pea
and Miss Annie a little while,

1:35:21.767 --> 1:35:24.061
till they finish working on the apartment.

1:35:29.316 --> 1:35:30.526
Where you gonna go?

1:35:33.320 --> 1:35:34.321
I'll figure it out.

1:35:37.157 --> 1:35:38.993
I'll go to your school tomorrow

1:35:39.618 --> 1:35:43.330
and get everything straightened out
with Ms. What's-Her-Face.

1:36:02.474 --> 1:36:03.559
Yo, Ma.

1:36:14.695 --> 1:36:17.031
Yo, hey, Titi. What's up?

1:36:17.865 --> 1:36:19.408
Um...

1:36:19.408 --> 1:36:21.952
Yeah, you-- you heard from my mother yet?

1:36:24.913 --> 1:36:29.710
Nah, I been--
I been trying to call her all morning.

1:36:29.710 --> 1:36:31.253
No, she, um...

1:36:32.338 --> 1:36:33.505
Yeah, just, um...

1:36:35.674 --> 1:36:38.385
Yeah, just give me a call back
when you-- when you do.

1:36:46.060 --> 1:36:47.937
Hey, y-yeah.

1:36:47.937 --> 1:36:50.189
Yeah, Aunt Kim. Hold on. Let me...

1:36:51.023 --> 1:36:53.150
Hey, no, let, uh--
let me give you a call back.

1:36:57.696 --> 1:37:00.616
Hi, Terrance. Is your mother home?

1:37:01.408 --> 1:37:02.534
Um...

1:37:03.410 --> 1:37:04.578
N-- No.

1:37:05.496 --> 1:37:06.872
She left for work already?

1:37:08.248 --> 1:37:11.418
Yeah, um, I think so.

1:37:14.338 --> 1:37:17.216
Do you mind if we come in
and talk for a bit?

1:37:18.133 --> 1:37:19.176
Uh...

1:37:20.094 --> 1:37:22.596
Yeah. I mean, yeah, yeah, yeah. Okay.

1:37:23.222 --> 1:37:24.556
Thank you.

1:37:25.432 --> 1:37:27.643
- This is Anne.
- Hey.

1:37:27.643 --> 1:37:31.063
And this is Officer Philips.
Officer Russo.

1:37:31.939 --> 1:37:33.190
May we have a seat?

1:37:34.650 --> 1:37:36.568
How long ago did she leave?

1:37:38.529 --> 1:37:39.780
Yesterday evening.

1:37:40.406 --> 1:37:42.866
What was the last thing
she said to you?

1:37:42.866 --> 1:37:45.202
Did she say anything
out of the ordinary?

1:37:45.202 --> 1:37:47.121
Anything unusual?

1:37:47.621 --> 1:37:51.292
Well... not that I remember.

1:37:52.126 --> 1:37:53.877
Everything seemed fine.

1:37:53.877 --> 1:37:55.337
Excuse me, sir, could you--
could you--

1:37:55.337 --> 1:37:58.215
could y'all, you know,
not go through all our stuff?

1:37:58.215 --> 1:38:00.884
Terrance, we really need
your cooperation on this.

1:38:00.884 --> 1:38:03.220
Uh, she, like, gonna get in trouble
or something?

1:38:03.220 --> 1:38:06.223
You know, 'cause, I mean,
you know, why does it even matter?

1:38:06.223 --> 1:38:08.809
I mean, you know,
I'm almost 18, you know, so.

1:38:10.477 --> 1:38:11.687
Um...

1:38:12.438 --> 1:38:13.606
Well, about that.

1:38:15.441 --> 1:38:18.819
It's difficult for me to say
what I have to say right now.

1:38:21.989 --> 1:38:22.990
Inez...

1:38:24.450 --> 1:38:26.160
is not your biological mother.

1:38:30.748 --> 1:38:31.790
N--

1:38:32.666 --> 1:38:34.501
Like some joke or something?

1:38:34.501 --> 1:38:35.836
No, it's not.

1:38:43.093 --> 1:38:45.054
This is the woman who abducted you.

1:38:47.932 --> 1:38:51.018
Whatever story she told you
was just a lie that she cooked up.

1:38:53.187 --> 1:38:55.898
I am so sorry
you have to find out like this.

1:38:55.898 --> 1:38:58.108
Are you sure
you don't know where she is?

1:38:58.108 --> 1:38:59.360
Any ideas at all?

1:39:01.278 --> 1:39:02.905
Give him some room, please.

1:39:05.032 --> 1:39:09.119
For now, we need to focus on
what's best for Terry moving forward.

1:39:09.119 --> 1:39:10.788
What's best for me?

1:39:10.788 --> 1:39:13.332
He doesn't have any known relatives
that we can trust.

1:39:13.332 --> 1:39:14.959
That's all right.

1:39:14.959 --> 1:39:17.503
We can place him at Sheltering Arms
for the time being.

1:39:18.629 --> 1:39:20.798
It's a family services program. It's...

1:39:20.798 --> 1:39:22.091
I know what it is.

1:39:22.091 --> 1:39:25.928
Just for a couple of weeks,
until we can navigate next steps.

1:39:29.682 --> 1:39:31.433
If that's all right with you.

1:39:33.477 --> 1:39:35.980
I don't know if your parents
are still on the street,

1:39:35.980 --> 1:39:37.731
but we can work on that.

1:39:39.650 --> 1:39:41.610
Everything was such a mess back then.

1:39:43.737 --> 1:39:46.407
In my office, the only record
you had on some kids was...

1:39:48.242 --> 1:39:49.743
just an index card.

1:39:57.251 --> 1:39:58.377
Hello?

1:39:59.253 --> 1:40:00.963
- Terry, is that you?

1:40:00.963 --> 1:40:03.632
<i>Yeah. Y-- Titi--</i>

1:40:04.758 --> 1:40:08.304
I stopped by the group home, but
nobody seems to know where you are.

1:40:08.304 --> 1:40:09.888
<i>I'm at-- I'm at a pay phone.</i>

1:40:09.888 --> 1:40:12.349
<i>I can't stay there.</i>

1:40:12.349 --> 1:40:13.934
You want to meet me back here?

1:40:15.019 --> 1:40:17.354
<i>I want you to come stay with me.</i>

1:40:17.354 --> 1:40:19.523
- Yeah.
-<i>Okay.</i>

1:40:19.523 --> 1:40:22.151
<i>I think you should
stop by the house first,</i>

1:40:22.151 --> 1:40:24.903
pick up any last things
you might want to take with you.

1:40:27.281 --> 1:40:28.699
Yeah.

1:40:28.699 --> 1:40:31.243
-<i>I'll see you soon, baby.</i>
- Okay.

1:40:33.621 --> 1:40:34.747
Okay.

1:41:09.323 --> 1:41:11.992
- Ma?
- Hey, Terry.

1:41:17.289 --> 1:41:18.874
What you-- What you doing?

1:41:20.000 --> 1:41:21.335
I left some things.

1:41:22.169 --> 1:41:24.213
Look, don't stand over there
looking over me.

1:41:24.213 --> 1:41:27.466
I'm sure they already got to you,
so feel free to run along.

1:41:31.428 --> 1:41:32.763
Can we talk, though?

1:41:33.514 --> 1:41:34.682
Talk about what?

1:41:35.808 --> 1:41:37.101
You serious right now?

1:41:40.187 --> 1:41:42.690
Fine. You want to talk, let's talk.

1:41:52.032 --> 1:41:53.534
Fetch me my Newports.

1:41:55.494 --> 1:41:57.830
- You was just over there...
- Over on the stand.

1:42:11.844 --> 1:42:13.178
What you want me to say?

1:42:13.846 --> 1:42:15.639
That I fucked up?

1:42:15.639 --> 1:42:17.474
Yeah, T, I fucked up.

1:42:17.474 --> 1:42:18.809
But life goes on. So what?

1:42:18.809 --> 1:42:20.394
Well, as long as it's your call, right?

1:42:20.394 --> 1:42:22.521
Who was the one who made the choice,
standing in that hospital?

1:42:22.521 --> 1:42:24.273
- Was it you or me?
- Thinking you was my fucking mother!

1:42:24.273 --> 1:42:25.691
Lower your fucking tone!

1:42:26.567 --> 1:42:29.069
You better watch
how the fuck you talking to me.

1:42:31.405 --> 1:42:32.406
Did Lucky know?

1:42:37.911 --> 1:42:39.496
Yes, he knew.

1:42:41.415 --> 1:42:43.667
He didn't agree with it, but he knew.

1:42:44.835 --> 1:42:46.920
Why? Why you do it?

1:42:52.760 --> 1:42:54.470
I don't know why I did it, T.

1:42:54.470 --> 1:42:57.181
It was something small
that turned into something else.

1:42:57.181 --> 1:42:59.099
And that's supposed
to make it right or something?

1:42:59.099 --> 1:43:01.101
Who made you the chief
of right or wrong?

1:43:02.311 --> 1:43:04.229
You don't think I have feelings too?

1:43:04.229 --> 1:43:07.775
After all those years I took care of you,
who the fuck was there to take care of me?

1:43:07.775 --> 1:43:10.694
I stood up for everybody else!
What the fuck was it for?

1:43:11.779 --> 1:43:13.364
Every chance you had,

1:43:13.364 --> 1:43:15.991
every chance you had,
you turned your back on me!

1:43:15.991 --> 1:43:17.952
- That's not true.
- Oh, please.

1:43:17.952 --> 1:43:20.454
Nobody else give a shit about Black women
except for other Black women,

1:43:20.454 --> 1:43:22.456
and even that shit get messy.

1:43:29.296 --> 1:43:31.298
Who heard me when I was hurt?

1:43:33.968 --> 1:43:35.135
It wasn't you.

1:43:35.970 --> 1:43:37.554
And it damn sure wasn't Lucky.

1:43:37.554 --> 1:43:39.223
But you were my mother!

1:43:40.849 --> 1:43:44.144
Mmm? Now, how am I supposed to feel?

1:44:02.913 --> 1:44:05.332
I need to know what was real.

1:44:20.514 --> 1:44:22.683
I never left you on that corner.

1:44:26.020 --> 1:44:27.730
I was the one that found you.

1:44:32.359 --> 1:44:36.363
Little two-year-old
running around outside the shelter.

1:44:40.034 --> 1:44:43.787
I waited outside on that block
for hours with you.

1:44:45.956 --> 1:44:48.626
Waiting for anybody to show up.

1:44:50.878 --> 1:44:53.422
I saw so much of myself.

1:44:56.383 --> 1:44:59.553
I just... I just wanted
to look out for you.

1:45:01.972 --> 1:45:04.308
I didn't want you getting chewed out
like I was.

1:45:06.018 --> 1:45:09.146
I seen somebody who needed me.

1:45:09.146 --> 1:45:10.314
But...

1:45:11.357 --> 1:45:13.901
But maybe I'm the one who needed you.

1:45:15.027 --> 1:45:16.862
And, T, for that, I'm sorry.

1:45:18.739 --> 1:45:20.699
I'm... I'm sorry.

1:45:25.579 --> 1:45:27.081
I tried to change.

1:45:30.000 --> 1:45:33.253
But I don't-- I don't want it.
I don't want this.

1:45:34.922 --> 1:45:38.384
Not if... Not if it's built on a lie.

1:45:40.094 --> 1:45:44.431
Not if being loved by you or anybody else
means not loving myself.

1:45:47.142 --> 1:45:49.478
They not gonna let you get away with it.

1:45:49.478 --> 1:45:50.771
I ain't going to jail.

1:45:51.480 --> 1:45:54.066
I already know what the fuck
they gonna say anyway.

1:45:54.066 --> 1:45:55.693
Already know. And guess what?

1:45:55.693 --> 1:45:57.736
I don't give a fuck.

1:45:57.736 --> 1:45:59.321
Because I still won.

1:46:00.781 --> 1:46:02.032
I won.

1:46:03.075 --> 1:46:05.786
Because I know you gonna grow up
to be somebody.

1:46:10.416 --> 1:46:13.085
I wish I didn't know.

1:46:16.046 --> 1:46:19.717
I wish-- I wish you could've did a better
job of keeping that lie to yourself.

1:46:20.634 --> 1:46:24.013
I wish it could've continued
so that we could've continued, and I...

1:46:27.683 --> 1:46:29.560
I wish I knew how to be better to you

1:46:29.560 --> 1:46:32.229
so you didn't feel like
you had to leave me alone.

1:46:36.066 --> 1:46:37.484
'Cause I'm scared.

1:46:41.071 --> 1:46:43.741
I'm scared
that I won't have no home no more.

1:46:45.117 --> 1:46:46.577
And one day I'm gonna show up,

1:46:46.577 --> 1:46:49.246
and it's gonna feel like
we ain't never happened.

1:46:51.081 --> 1:46:52.499
Ma!

1:46:53.417 --> 1:46:55.461
Like this wasn't our living room?

1:46:57.087 --> 1:46:58.255
Our home?

1:47:02.676 --> 1:47:04.678
I miss my bed, Ma.

1:47:09.683 --> 1:47:11.685
The one that you made for me.

1:47:21.195 --> 1:47:22.905
Where's home for me now?

1:49:38.248 --> 1:49:39.833
This isn't goodbye.

1:49:41.835 --> 1:49:45.172
I promise. This isn't goodbye, T.

1:49:47.007 --> 1:49:48.175
I promise.

1:49:54.848 --> 1:49:56.100
I love you, Ma.

1:50:00.020 --> 1:50:01.230
I love you.

1:50:06.277 --> 1:50:07.736
